      "message": "https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/main:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/server/auth/realms/realms.go;l\u003d26-27\n\nLogID is part of the LogName, and is not used to identify each LogEntry. If two projects are mapped to the same LogID, they will appear in the same LogName(s).\n: https://screencast.googleplex.com/cast/NjYyODY2MjI4NTY5NzAyNHwxODg5NGM5NS1jMA\n\nThis may not be that bad. Users can still search logs by the projecct name, using resource.labels.project_id \u003d \"full_project_string\"",
