      "message": "The realms.go doesn\u0027t validate project name at the time of LUCI project registration. The above validation will kick in later down the road.\n\n\u003e LogID is part of the LogName, and is not used to identify each LogEntry\n\nYes, I posted my above comment with this in mind.\nMy point is that there is no advantage in the degraded performance silently kicked in on the highly-unlikely-very-long-project-name.\nGiven the rarity, hard failure is good enough and code becomes much simpler \"logdog/\" + sa.project.\n\n\nMeta: this is a bikeshed, I only comment because you made code more complex than necessary. If this is dear to you, keep it.",
